        // Mimic the pattern seen: the memory after the 128-byte table
        // apparently contains certain values. We use the serial type length
        // formula for blob/text: even types are blobs, odd are text,
        // length = (serial_type - 12) / 2
        // But test shows 220->1 which doesn't fit that formula.
        // The only way to get 1 for 220 is if the table wraps: 220 % 128 = 92
        // SQLITE3_SMALL_TYPE_SIZES[92] = 40, not 1 either.
        // Try treating as signed: 220 as i8 = -36, still unclear.
